description: Lists the agents of the assessment runs that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment runs.

parameters.name: assessmentRunArn
parameters.description: The ARN that specifies the assessment run whose agents you want to list.

parameters.name: filter
parameters.description: You can use this parameter to specify a subset of data to be included in the action's response. For a record to match a filter, all specified filter attributes must match. When multiple values are specified for a filter attribute, any of the values can match. The current health state of the agent. Values can be set to HEALTHY or UNHEALTHY. (string) --- The detailed health state of the agent. Values can be set to IDLE, RUNNING, SHUTDOWN, UNHEALTHY, THROTTLED, and UNKNOWN. (string) ---

nested_items.name: assessmentRunAgents
nested_items.description: A list of ARNs that specifies the agents returned by the action.

nested_items.name: agentId
nested_items.description: The AWS account of the EC2 instance where the agent is installed.

nested_items.name: assessmentRunArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the assessment run that is associated with the agent.

nested_items.name: agentHealth
nested_items.description: The current health state of the agent.

nested_items.name: agentHealthCode
nested_items.description: The detailed health state of the agent.

nested_items.name: agentHealthDetails
nested_items.description: The description for the agent health code.

nested_items.name: autoScalingGroup
nested_items.description: The Auto Scaling group of the EC2 instance that is specified by the agent ID.

nested_items.name: telemetryMetadata
nested_items.description: The Amazon Inspector application data metrics that are collected by the agent.

nested_items.name: messageType
nested_items.description: A specific type of behavioral data that is collected by the agent.

nested_items.name: count
nested_items.description: The count of messages that the agent sends to the Amazon Inspector service.

nested_items.name: dataSize
nested_items.description: The data size of messages that the agent sends to the Amazon Inspector service.
